        <mxCell id="sr3Lcem74erj5iztOOXT-7" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;This diagram illustrates the backend management and regulatory oversight functions required to maintain platform integrity and financial compliance. It focuses on administrative controls like account freezing and rate updates, while enabling auditors to review transaction histories and&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;generate mandatory compliance reports.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Key Actors&lt;/b&gt;: Bank Admin (Internal controller) and Auditor (Compliance validator).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
